Notwithstanding subsection (a)(1) of this section, an association is eligible for continued membership in the Fund beyond its scheduled date of termination, but in no event beyond October 30, 1987, if the Fund Director and the Secretary of Labor, Licensing, and Regulation find:
The association has made a good faith effort to obtain insurance from the Federal Savings and Loan Insurance Corporation or other federal agency;
There is a substantial likelihood that the association will qualify for federal insurance;
The failure to obtain federal insurance is not attributable to unjustified delay on the part of the association; and
The interest of the savings account holders will not be jeopardized.
